title: Trabaci - Keyboard Music 7 - S Vartolo (2000) [Philidor; FLAC]
description:
Giovanni Maria Trabaci was considered in the first half of the 17th century among the Italian States' greatest keyboard performers and composers. His work partakes of the freedom of form that was common to the early Baroque, when fantasias went by many names, and composers wrote down their celebrated improvisations to publish, later. This series of releases has Silvio Vartolo performing on harpsichord, organ, and a spinet, a smaller harpsichord usually meant for more intimate music-making.

Transfers are made at 768 kBits/s, directly from the disc.

Bio enclosed. You can find all my classical uploads by searching on Philidor, or in this thread:
